==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Indigestion
<hw>In`di*ges"tion</hw> <pr>(?; 106)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>indigestio</ets>: cf. F. <ets>indigestion</ets>. See <er>In-</er>
not, and <er>Digest</er>.]</ety> <def>Discomfort due to a lack of proper
digestive action; a failure of the normal changes which food should
undergo in the alimentary canal; dyspepsia; incomplete or difficult
digestion.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Indigitate</ent>⟦br⟧
